# Maven Conventions

## POM Structure
- Use `<dependencyManagement>` with BOMs for version centralization
- Pin all dependency versions explicitly -- no dynamic ranges
- Properties for version strings: `<spring-boot.version>4.0.5</spring-boot.version>`
- Standard directory layout: `src/main/java`, `src/test/java`, `src/main/resources`

## Maven Wrapper
- Always use Maven Wrapper (`mvnw` / `mvnw.cmd`)
- Commit `.mvn/wrapper/` to version control
- JVM args in `.mvn/maven.config`

## Dependency Management
- Import Spring Boot BOM: `spring-boot-dependencies` in `<dependencyManagement>`
- Separate test dependencies with `<scope>test</scope>`
- Review new dependencies for license, maintenance status, and CVEs
- Run `./mvnw dependency:tree` to audit transitive dependencies

## Plugin Management
- Centralize plugins in `<pluginManagement>` in parent POM
- Required plugins: Surefire (unit tests), Failsafe (integration tests), JaCoCo (coverage), Enforcer (constraints)
- Checkstyle/Spotless for formatting enforcement

## Multi-Module Projects
- Root POM defines `<modules>`, shared properties, and managed dependencies
- Child POMs inherit from root; no hardcoded versions
- Check for: version drift across siblings, redundant plugin config, properties that should be centralized

## Build Commands
- `./mvnw validate` -- pre-change validation
- `./mvnw compile` -- compilation check (blocking gate)
- `./mvnw clean verify` -- full build with tests
- `./mvnw clean install -DskipTests` -- install to local repo (skip only when justified)

